  "name": "M. M. Azizul Islam Rasel",
  "title": "Senior Lecturer",
  "department": "General Education Program (GED)",
  "school": "",
  "profile_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/faculty/m-m-azizul-islam-rasel",
  "photo_url": "https://ulab.edu.bd/sites/default/files/styles/faculty_avatar/public/images/faculty/M%20M%20Azizul%20Islam.jpg?itok=r53_Q6vp",
  "bio_raw": "He is a historian. Apart from historical studies he is interested in critical theory and Marxism. He was educated in Dhaka and Leiden University, with prestigious Encompas Scholarship. He has authored a number of academic articles. He has presented papers in several national and international conferences among which include Center for South Asian Studies, Hawaii University, USA and Bangladesh Itihas Samiti and Itihas Sammiloni. He has published a book titled The Seventeenth Century Dutch Travel Literature and the Production of Knowledge on Asia (2013). Currently He is researching on Communalism in Pakistan (East Bengal, 1947-1955) and Indigenous history and society.\nCreative Works:\nPublished poems and short stories in the national dailies and little magazines.",
  "stated_interests": [
    "South Asian History, Global History, Early Modern and Modern History, History of Bengal, History of Bangladesh, Labour History, Intellectual History, Social and Cultural History."
  ],
  "education": [
    {
      "raw": "Education\nBA in History\n, University of Dhaka, Bangladesh.\nMA in History\n, University of Dhaka, Bangladesh.\nMA in History\n, Leiden University, the Netherlands."
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Books\nThe Seventeenth Century Dutch Travel Literature and the Production of Knowledge on Asia (2013)\nReview of 1971: A Global History of the Creation of Bangladesh by Srinath Raghavan . New Delhi: Permanent Black, 2013. In Protichinta, 2014, 9th issue, 2014.\nReview of The Bengal Delta: Ecology, State and Social Change, 1840-1943 by Iftekhar Iqbal. Basingstoke: Palgrave Macmillan, 2010. In Protichinta, 3(2), 2013. pp. 147-157.\nExperiencing the Border: The Lushai People and Transnational Space’ in Reece Jones and Md. Azmeary Ferdoush (eds.), Borders and Mobility: South Asia and Beyond (Amsterdam:Amsterdam University Press, 2018), pp.81-97\nDutch Trade in Bengal, c. Seventeenth and Eighteenth Centuries’ in Abdul Momin Chowdhury (ed.), History of Bangladesh, 1200-1704 CE, vol.3 (Dhaka: Asiatic Society of Bangladesh, forthcoming)\nReview of 1971: A Global History of the Creation of Bangladesh by Srinath Raghavan . New Delhi: Permanent Black, 2013. In Protichinta, 2014, 9th issue, 2014.\nReview of The Bengal Delta: Ecology, State and Social Change, 1840-1943 by Iftekhar Iqbal. Basingstoke: Palgrave Macmillan, 2010. In Protichinta, 3(2), 2013. pp. 147-157.",
